{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I was introduced to the Shakespeare authorship question for the first time in a high school literature class. I admit now that I didn’t give the argument much thought. My English teacher didn’t sound entirely convinced, either. I also never did put much stock in the Cult of Personality. I wanted to read “Othello,” not debate who wrote “Othello.” I left that question to those with more government or institutional funding. But as I pursued my life in books, the tittering never stopped. Did Shakespeare really write Shakespeare?</p>","frontmatter":{"hero":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='230' viewBox='0 0 400 230' version='1'%3e%3cpath d='M38 9l-7 1h-4v4c2 8 4 14 8 18l4 6 4 1 3-1 3-5c4-5 6-10 7-18V9H38m-4 5v6h7c8-1 8-1 8-4 0-2 0-3-6-3l-9 1m-6 41v7h345V47H28v8m4 22v6h17c15 0 17 0 17 2h2a170 170 0 0 1 47-1l4-1c3 0 3 0 3-5v-6h-13l-45-1H32v6m59-1c-1 3-2 3 14 3l14-1c0-2-4-4-7-3H93c-1-1-2-1-2 1m-58 26v11h19V90H33v12m283 10v5c0 4 0 5 3 5l4 1h2l21-1h21v-9l-26-1h-25m0 19c0 4 0 5 2 4l4 1h2l22-1h20v-8h-50v4m0 18v7h3l4 1h1l21-1h21v-15h-50v8m0 17c0 3 0 4 2 4l4 1h2l22-1h20v-9h-50v5m-284-3l1 51 8-1h8l2-5c3-4 5-7 7-7l-1 6-3 6c1 0 4-3 4-5l1-2v5c-1 2-1 2 4 2 6 0 6 0 3-4v-3l2 4c2 4 3 4 3 0v-4l2 2c0 5 1 5 23 5h26v-51H78l-46 1m284 12v5c0 4 0 5 3 5l4 1h2l21-1h21v-9l-26-1h-25m0 22v8h3l4 1h1l21-1h21v-16h-50v8m0 18c0 4 0 4 2 4l5 2h2c0-2 3-2 21-2h21v-9h-51v5m0 12c0 3 3 4 3 1h1c0 2 2 3 2 1s15-2 16 0l14 1h14v-6h-50v3' fill='lightgray' fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":1.740547588005215,"src":"/static/3c60356412a777e63d5929e50cafd8e3/6ceba/shakespeare-the-man-the-myth-the-doubt.png","srcSet":"/static/3c60356412a777e63d5929e50cafd8e3/af310/shakespeare-the-man-the-myth-the-doubt.png 200w,\n/static/3c60356412a777e63d5929e50cafd8e3/9f336/shakespeare-the-man-the-myth-the-doubt.png 400w,\n/static/3c60356412a777e63d5929e50cafd8e3/6ceba/shakespeare-the-man-the-myth-